Observations when running palha solver on branch "debug_TaylorGreen":

-----------------------------------------------------------------
1) For parameters:
d=2, deg=1, n_t=100, Delta_t = 1/100, n_el = 16,

The results are shown in Fig.1, show wierd behavior for the explicit Euler because it gives a "negative pressure" that the pH solver maintains this trend which is opposite to the exact solution. THe 1st inital step also gives a spike in the vorticity plot and thus the Enstrophy.

Will repeat experiment for refined mesh and higher degrees to confirm observation.

--> d=2, deg=2, n_t=100, Delta_t = 1/100, n_el = 16, --> Explicit Euler does not converge even up to 1/1000 !!
--> d=2, deg=1, n_t=100, Delta_t = 1/100, n_el = 32, --> Lower spikes observed but higher dual pressure initial error --> Fig_2
--> d=3, deg=1, n_t=100, Delta_t = 1/100, n_el = 8, --> It is clear here that the explicit EUler gives a negative pressure, but the NS solver fixes it onwards and we see a flip in the pressure --> Fig_3

